column3: It represents the values true(1) and false(0).
The Unix time stamp is a way to track time as a running total of seconds. This count starts at the Unix Epoch on January 1st, 1970 at UTC.
Well-known text (WKT) is a text markup language for representing vector geometry objects. A binary equivalent, known as well-known binary (WKB).
It is used to store a single letter, digit, punctuation mark, symbol, or blank space.
